title: Omens and Superstitions of Southern India
creator: Edgar Thurston
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of Omens and Superstitions of Southern India, by Edgar Thurston. This book deals mainly with some aspects of what may be termed the psychical life of the inhabitants of the Madras Presidency, and the Native States of Travancore and Cochin. For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
